ls0 ws0">1. </div><div class="t m1c7a x6f h4 y1b6b ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">What is the greatest victory we can achieve? Prov. 16: 32. </div><div class="t m127 x64 h4 y1ab9 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">2. </div><div class="t m1961 x6f h4 y1b13 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">What is one able to do who can control his words? James </div><div class="t m16cc x49 h4 y168f ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">3: 2. Note 1. </div><div class="t m2b6 x64 h4 y63f ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">3. </div><div class="t m10ad x6f h4 y138e ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">What evil is in the power of an unruly tongue? Verses </div><div class="t ma69 x49 h4 y1e97 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">4-6. </div><div class="t ma2 x64 h4 y1b22 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">4. </div><div class="t m9f2 x6f h4 y1edc ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">How did Christ emphasize the importance of our words? </div><div class="t m498 x59 h4 y133d ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Matt. 12: 34-37. Note 2. </div><div class="t m1cd x29 h4 y1bff ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">5. </div><div class="t m6ef x6f h4 y1bfe ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">What promise of victory over our thoughts is given us? </div><div class="t m18af x59 h4 y1d5b ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">2 Cor. 10: 4, 5. Note 3. </div><div class="t m1d0 x29 h4 y1c96 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">6. </div><div class="t m96f x34 h4 y1715 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Upon what should we think? Phil. 4: 8. Note 4. </div><div class="t m1d2 x29 h4 y1d5c ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">7. </div><div class="t m28be x6f h4 y1111 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">What instruction does the apostle Peter give concerning </div><div class="t me58 x59 h4 y1b91 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">the control of the mind? 1 Peter 1: 13. Note 5. </div><div class="t m1d5 x64 h4 y1dcc ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">8. </div><div class="t m528 x34 h4 y1662 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">How is the difficulty of controlling the tongue illustrated? </div><div class="t m19d7 x59 h4 y142c ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">James 3: 7, 8. </div><div class="t m127 x64 h4 y1d62 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">9.